  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\n\"Gas required exceeds allowance\" error coming from RPC whenever I attempt to deploy a modified ERC-20 token on Optimism using remix IDE. Pure ERC-20 token works flawlessly, but the one which calls additional contracts in its constructor is showing that error and prevents deployment.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. https://pastebin.com/ecGjemi2 - use this code for ERC-20 token, the most important part is _updateRouterV2(0x744776F27080b584D447A780ba260c435f3aE7d5); which I think causes the error\r\n3. Paste it in remix and compile with Optimizer enabled, 200 runs\r\n4. Preferably use Injected MetaMask provider to attempt the deployment\r\n5. See this error \r\n![image](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/assets/66825147/648f6cf7-0ced-4967-9b66-1d3313b64278)\r\n6. After force-sending the transaction fails by spending full 3M of gas, however successful deployment will require 4.3M of gas (tried the same on BSC)\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nContract should deploy without errors with correctly adjusted gas limit\r\n",
